# WezTerm Configuration Guidelines

## Core Configuration Areas
- Font and rendering settings
- Color schemes and themes
- Key bindings and shortcuts
- Window and tab management
- Integration with system

## Font Configuration
```lua
config.font = wezterm.font("CaskaydiaCove Nerd Font", {weight = "Light"})
config.font_size = 12.0
config.line_height = 1.4
```

## Theme Integration
- Support for multiple color schemes
- Match window manager theme
- Easy theme switching
- Transparency and blur effects for modern look

## Key Bindings
- Consistent with system shortcuts
- Tab management (Ctrl+Shift+T, Ctrl+PageUp/Down)
- Pane splitting and navigation
- Integration with Fish shell features

## Performance Optimizations
- GPU acceleration when available
- Efficient scrollback buffer
- Fast startup time
- Minimal resource usage

## Window Management
- Smart tab bar (hide when single tab)
- Window padding and margins
- Integration with tiling window managers
- Multi-monitor support

## Fish Shell Integration
- Proper shell integration
- Support for Fish completions
- Compatible with Fish abbreviations
- Terminal-specific Fish functions
